Krasny Bor 

February 1943. Krasny Bor, south of Leningrad

Krasny Bor was a substantial town of brick dwellings, lying astride both the Moscow-to-Leningrad highway and the October Railway. Just before midnight on 9 Feb 1943, Spaniards had been warned of an imminent Soviet attack on the exposed Spanish positions at Krasny Bor on the eastern bank of the Ishora river. The Soviets had massed an impressive forced to crush the Spanish defenders and clear the main Moscow-to-Leningrad highway upon which the eastern lines of the Spanish Blue Division were positioned.

Autor: Santiago Fuertes

